Mobile hamburger menu patch for oulu-hemodynamic
================================================

1) index.html
-------------
In the header, immediately after the brand link closing </a>, add:

<button class="menu-toggle" type="button" aria-label="Open navigation menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="mainNav">
  <span></span>
  <span></span>
  <span></span>
</button>

Then change:

<nav class="nav" aria-label="Main navigation">

To:

<nav class="nav" id="mainNav" aria-label="Main navigation">

2) styles.css
-------------
Append the full contents of `styles-css-addition.css` to the end of `styles.css`.

Because this addition is placed at the end of the stylesheet, it overrides the existing mobile rule that currently hides `.nav` under 920 px.

3) script.js
------------
Inside function setup(), after this block:

  document.querySelectorAll(".lang-btn").forEach((button) => {
    button.addEventListener("click", () => setLanguage(button.dataset.lang));
  });

Insert the full contents of `script-js-change.js`.
